#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:2
msgid "WAF"
msgstr "WAF"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:5
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:8
msgid "概念"
msgstr "Concept"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:9
msgid ""
"WAF（Web Application "
"Firewall，Web应用防火墙）是通过执行一系列针对HTTP/HTTPS的安全策略来专门为Web应用提供加固的产品。"
msgstr ""
"A WAF (Web Application Firewall) is a product designed to harden web "
"applications by enforcing a set of security policies for HTTP/HTTPS."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:11
msgid "在市场上，有各种价格各种功能和选项的WAF。在一定程度上，WAF能为Web应用提供安全性，但是不能保证完全的安全。"
msgstr "The market offers WAF products at many price points and with many functions and options. To some extent, a WAF can improve security for web applications, but it cannot guarantee complete security."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:14
msgid "常见功能"
msgstr "Common Features"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:15
msgid "检测异常协议，拒绝不符合HTTP标准的请求"
msgstr "Detect abnormal protocols and reject requests that do not comply with HTTP standards"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:16
msgid "对状态管理进行会话保护"
msgstr "Provide session protection for state management"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:17
msgid "Cookies保护"
msgstr "Cookie protection"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:18
msgid "信息泄露保护"
msgstr "Information disclosure protection"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:19
msgid "DDoS防护"
msgstr "DDoS protection"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:20
msgid "禁止某些IP访问"
msgstr "Block access from certain IP addresses"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:21
msgid "可疑IP检查"
msgstr "Suspicious IP checks"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:22
msgid "安全HTTP头管理"
msgstr "Secure HTTP header management"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:23
msgid "X-XSS-Protection"
msgstr "X-XSS-Protection"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:24
msgid "X-Frame-Options"
msgstr "X-Frame-Options"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:25
msgid "机制检测"
msgstr "Mechanism detection"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:26
msgid "CSRF token"
msgstr "CSRF token"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:27
msgid "HSTS"
msgstr "HSTS"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:30
msgid "布置位置"
msgstr "Deployment Location"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:31
msgid ""
"按布置位置，WAF可以分为云WAF、主机防护软件和硬件防护。云WAF布置在云上，请求先经过云服务器而后流向主机。主机防护软件需要主机预先安装对应软件，如mod_security"
"、ngx-lua-waf等，对主机进行防护。硬件防护指流量流向主机时，先经过设备的清洗和拦截。"
msgstr ""
"By deployment location, WAFs can be divided into cloud WAFs, host protection"
" software, and hardware protection. A cloud WAF is deployed in the cloud, so"
" requests first pass through the cloud service and then flow to the host. "
"Host protection software requires the corresponding software, such as "
"mod_security or ngx-lua-waf, to be installed on the host in advance. "
"Hardware protection means traffic is cleaned and intercepted by an appliance"
" before it reaches the host."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:34
msgid "防护方式"
msgstr "Protection Methods"

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:35
msgid "WAF常用的方法有关键字检测、正则表达式检测、语法分析、行为分析、声誉分析、机器学习等。"
msgstr "Common WAF methods include keyword detection, regular-expression detection, syntax analysis, behavior analysis, reputation analysis, and machine learning."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:37
msgid "基于正则的保护是最常见的保护方式。开发者用一些设定好的正则规则来检测载荷是否存在攻击性。基于正则的防护较为简单，因此存在一些缺点。例如只能应用于单次请求，而且正则很难应用到一些复杂的协议上。"
msgstr "Regular-expression-based protection is the most common protection method. Developers use predefined regular-expression rules to detect whether a payload is malicious. Regex-based protection is relatively simple and therefore has drawbacks. For example, it can only be applied to a single request, and regular expressions are difficult to apply to some complex protocols."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:39
msgid "基于语法的分析相对正则来说更快而且更准确，这种分析会把载荷按照语法解析成的符号组，然后在符号组中寻找危险的关键字。这种方式对一些载荷的变式有较好的效果，但是同样的，对解析器要求较高。"
msgstr "Syntax-based analysis is faster and more accurate than regular expressions. This analysis parses a payload into token groups according to syntax, then searches those token groups for dangerous keywords. This method works well against some payload variants, but it also places higher requirements on the parser."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:41
msgid "基于行为的分析着眼的范围更广一些，例如攻击者的端口扫描行为、目录爆破、参数测试或者一些其他自动化或者攻击的模式都会被纳入考虑之中。"
msgstr "Behavior-based analysis has a broader scope. For example, an attacker's port scanning, directory brute forcing, parameter testing, and other automation or attack patterns can all be considered."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:43
msgid "基于声誉的分析可以比较好的过滤掉一些可疑的来源，例如常用的VPN、匿名代理、Tor节点、僵尸网络节点的IP等。"
msgstr "Reputation-based analysis can filter suspicious sources effectively, such as IP addresses from commonly used VPNs, anonymous proxies, Tor nodes, and botnet nodes."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:45
msgid "基于机器学习的WAF涉及到的范围非常广，效果也因具体实现和场景而较为多样化。"
msgstr "Machine-learning-based WAFs cover a very broad range, and their effectiveness varies significantly with the specific implementation and scenario."

#: ../../source/misc/waf.rst:47
msgid "除了按具体的方法分，也可以根据白名单和黑名单的使用来分类。基于白名单的WAF适用于稳定的Web应用，而基于黑名单则适合处理已知问题。"
msgstr "In addition to classification by specific method, WAFs can also be classified by their use of whitelists and blacklists. Whitelist-based WAFs are suitable for stable web applications, while blacklist-based WAFs are suitable for handling known issues."

